<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Pilsburry on 05-26-2002 10:17 AM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">The thing is they deactivated snare on boss mobs....

CH still works.

However CH is our ONLY real definitive skill that makes us go from non-functional to god.

I mean what do we do on a raid?
CH - ok, great
DL - druids have similar
CE - shaman have similar for non-tanks
AEGO - You can get more hp using a different combo, and PoG will end up giving 6mana/tick more.
Rez - OK were the best at this, but paladin comes close, and necro is actually better at this but requires sacrifices (necros can FD in camp)
NUKE - resisted more then dru/mag/wiz...worse ratio. Definately not our calling.

So in otherwords deactivate CH and druids would pass up us in desireability...except for rez's.

Plus in regular groups the situation would continue....and for solo they aready blow us away.

The only difference would be YES. You would require them in larger numbers. That just would mean you would have 28 druids who can heal OR nuke OR evac OR snare OR DoT. Every exp group would have 3 druids, except the druids would probably still solo because they are so powerful solo.

Basically the world would instantly become overrrun with druids. Maybe 50% of the norrath population or more.

